- Things to modify when deploying on another machine
    - ports configuration
        - to run client on port XX:
            - for development: PORT=XX in [root]/.env file.
            - for production: npx serve [path-to-build-folder] -l XX
            - Modify "Access-Control-Allow_Origin" header for server. 
                - [root]/server/index.js : res.header("Access-Control-Allow-Origin", "https://[IP-addr]:XX");)
        - to run server on port XX:
            - [root]/server/index.js : console.log("\n\n[Server] Starting server on port XX")
            - [root]/server/index.js : app.listen(XX, '0.0.0.0');
            - [root]/client/src/config.js : module.exports.server = 'http://localhost:XX'

- Extras
    - Enable service worker for performance(but only on deployment)